place_name: 2024 Car-Free Jamsu Bridge Tubeok Tubeok Festival
description: The "Car-Free Shambridge Walking Festival" has become a representative festival of the Han River and a healing playground that everyone can enjoy together. This fall, the car-free Shambridge Walking Festival will return with more novel and colorful entertainment programs. The Seoul City announced that the "Shambridge Walking Festival" will be held from September 1 to October 27 (every Sunday, 13:00 to 21:00) at the Banpo Han River Park Shambridge and Moonlight Plaza area.In the first half of the festival, the talent show "Han River Rising Star", "Mask Parade" and "Motorboat Parade" were loved by many people. In this festival, the themes of "Art", "Games", "Health" and "Rest" where you can feel healing while watching the rainbow fountain are prepared to meet different preferences.
